File: Desmond Tutu, Nobel Peace Laureate and Archbishop Emeritus attends the Desmond Tutu Peace lecture, which coincides with his birthday, on October 07, 2019, in Cape Town. JOHANNESBURG - Archbishop Emeritus Desmond Tutu has been admitted to hospital for treatment of a "stubborn" infection. Tutu has been hospitalised several times over the past few years for treatment of a similar condition. READ: Archie meets The Arch Last month the 88-year-old met the Springboks, praising them for their Rugby World Cup victory. The Nobel Peace Prize winner also urged the country to continue building on the momentum brought about by win.